				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${\sigma _{{\rm{Lorentz}}}} \lesssim 2 \times {10^{- 14}}{\rm{m}}/{{\rm{s}}^2},$$\end{document} which is negligible.

More recent infrared observations established an upper limit of 0.3 Earth masses of Kuiper Belt dust in the trans-Neptunian region [40, 363, 371]. Therefore, for the contribution of Kuiper belt gravity, the authors of [27] placed a limit of 5.8\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
