In contrast, to produce the observed acceleration, any propulsion system leaks would have had to be i) constant in time; ii) the same on both spacecraft; iii) not inducing any detectable changes in the spin rate or precession. Given these considerations, [27] conservatively estimates that undetected gas leaks introduce an uncertainty no greater than 5.13\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
