				\begin{document}$$S = - m{c^2}\int {{{\left({1 - 2{{U(x)} \over {{c^2}}} - {R^2}(t){{{{\dot x}^2}} \over {{c^2}}}} \right)}^{{1 \over 2}}}dt \approx \int {\left({- m{c^2} + mU(r) + {m \over 2}{R^2}(t)({{\dot r}^2} + {r^2}{{\dot \varphi}^2})} \right)dt.}}$$\end{document} In the case of weak time dependence of R(t) the action above has two adiabatic invariants: 6.22\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
