				\begin{document}$${\bf{F}}(t) = - \int {{\mathbb P}({\bf{x}},\,t) \cdot {\rm{d}}{\bf{A}},}$$\end{document} which, for an isotropic (Lambertian) emitter yields the well-known law 7.7\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
